The '''Great Madrasah''' was a [[madrasah]] (school) in [[Nicosia]], [[Cyprus]]. It was built in 1573 and it was the first madrasah in Cyprus. It included classrooms and dormitories and in 1828, a fountain was added. In 1936 the madrasah was demolished, but education continued until the 1939–40 academic year until finally being abandoned later in 1940. It was donated by [[Ismail Aga]], and owned by [[Evkaf Administration]].<ref>Gazioğlu, Ahmet C. (1990). The Turks in Cyprus: a province of the Ottoman Empire (1571–1878), 198, K. Rüstem.</ref><ref>Hakeri, Bener Hakkı. (1992). "Büyük Medrese". Kıbrıs Türk Ansiklopedisi I: 69. Kıbrıs Gazetesi Yayınları.</ref>

